STEP 1)
install java and git svn 
download svn-migration-scripts.jar (download in your home directory)
java -jar ~/svn-migration-scripts.jar authors http://anyscheduler.org/svn/anurag >> authors.txt
git svn clone --stdlayout --prefix='' --authors-file=authors.txt http://anyscheduler.org/svn/anurag/perl_project anurag
java -Dfile.encoding=utf-8 -jar ~/svn-migration-scripts.jar clean-git --force


add few files to the snv then run the following command
git svn fetch

after that run the following command to see the files in your current working directory
java -Dfile.encoding=utf-8 -jar ~/svn-migration-scripts.jar sync-rebase
java -Dfile.encoding=utf-8 -jar ~/svn-migration-scripts.jar clean-git --force


After this you need to share 
git remote add origin https://anurag939@bitbucket.org/anurag939/anurag.git
